3. Collects the ordered names by iterating through the set and calling `get()` on each reactive variable
4. Checks if all names are unique by verifying the set size equals 3 (since sets don't allow duplicates)
5. Returns the `OrderingSnapshot` with the results

The `React` handles are ordered based on their internal node pointers (as shown in the hash specialization fragment), and the set maintains this ordering. The uniqueness check ensures that all three reactive variables are distinct nodes in the dependency graph.

